Fine-tuning leverages pre-trained models for task-specific performance, requiring minimal training data. Fine-tuning is ideal for specific tasks like segmentation in computer vision or text summarization in NLP, demanding more resources than transfer learning.

Indexing methods include hash-based, tree-based, and graph-based approaches for fast and accurate searches.
